engineer-plotter.description: This page will allow you to plot an efficient route to engineer your ship.

engineer-plotter.title: Engineer Plotter

exact-plotter.description: This page will allow you to plot between two different star systems.  It will attempt to plot you an exact route, including fuel usage, neutron supercharges and injection boosts if so desired.
exact-plotter.edsy_profile_description: Submit your commander profile to ED:Shipyard so that you can export your current ship to SLEF.  This will open in a new window so you do not lose your place on the site.
exact-plotter.edsy_profile_instructions: Once you have the profile imported you can click Ops in the top right of ED:Shipyard and export your build.  You should copy the SLEF and paste it into the ship build box on the router.
exact-plotter.fuel_remaining_description: Fuel currently in the fuel tank.  This does not include the reserve tank
exact-plotter.load_profile_description: Load your current ship profile from the Frontier servers
exact-plotter.title: Galaxy Plotter
exact-plotter.warning: This router is in beta and the results are not guaranteed to be ideal, it may also route you through systems which require a permit.

fields.algorithm_description: Which routing algorithm to use, different algorithms may work faster, find better routes or in some cases be unable to find a route.
fields.allow_planetary_description: Include planetary stations in the route
Include Fleet Carriers owned by players in the route
fields.allow_prohibited_description: Include goods which are illegal in the destination system
fields.avoid_thargoids_description: Avoid systems that are at war with or controlled by the Thargoids.
fields.determine_required_fuel_description: Calculate how much Tritium would be required to complete the entire route.
fields.efficiency_description: Increase this to reduce how far off the direct route the system will plot to get to a neutron star (An efficiency of 100 will not deviate from the direct route in order to plot from A to B and will most likely break down the journey into 20000 LY blocks).
fields.engineers_description: List of engineers to use, select none in order to allow all engineers.
fields.exclude_secondary_description: Prevent the system using secondary neutron and scoopable stars to help with the route
fields.fuel_remaining_description: Tritium currently in the fuel tank.  You may have to transfer from the market to get it to this level
fields.icy_ring_description: Does the system have an icy ring?
fields.jumps_description: Estimated number of jumps to this system.
fields.loop_description: Force the route to return to the starting system.
fields.market_capacity_description: The amount of capacity taken up by the commodities in your market
fields.maximum_distance_description: Maximum distance the station can be from the arrival star
fields.maximum_hop_distance_description: Maximum distance between hops (this can be larger than your ship range)
fields.maximum_market_age_description: Maximum age the stations in the route can have had their market data updated
fields.maximum_systems_description: This is maximum number of systems that the plotter will route you through, lower this for a shorter trip.
fields.module_capacity_description: The amount of capacity taken up by the modules installed on your fleet carrier
fields.name: Name
fields.neutron_description: Is the star a neutron star?
fields.permit_description: Allow systems which require permits to be included in the run
fields.pristine_description: Is the ring reserve level pristine?
fields.requires_large_pad_description: Filter out stations which do not have a large pad
fields.restock_amount_description: The amount of tritium you need to aquire to restock
fields.restock_description: Do you need to restock tritium?
fields.scanned_description: Uncheck to mark a body as not scanned
fields.search_radius_description: This is the distance in LY around which the plotter will look for valuable worlds for you to visit.  A value of 25 LY tends to give a nice balance for A to B routes keeping the number of jumps reasonbly low whilst still giving a nice payout.  For circular routes (leaving destination blank) you will probably want to increase this to 100-500 LY.
fields.select_thargoid_war_failure_state: Select Thargoid war state after failure
fields.select_thargoid_war_success_state: Select Thargoid war state after success
fields.ship_build_description: Paste ship build JSON exported from https://coriolis.io or SLEF from https://edsy.org
fields.terraforming_description: Is the body a terraformable candidate?
fields.time_description: Amount of time to spend calculating the route (in seconds, more time should produce shorter routes)
fields.tritium_fuel_description: The amount of tritium in your fuel tank
fields.tritium_market_description: The amount of tritium in your commodities market
fields.unique_description: Prevent the system revisiting stations which are already in the route
fields.used_capacity_description: Fill in the capacity shown in the upper right corner of the carrier managment screen.
fields.use_injections_description: Use FSD synthesis to boost when a neutron star is not available.
fields.use_mapping_value_description: Use the mapping value rather than the scan value
fields.use_supercharge_description: Use neutron stars to supercharge your FSD

fields_help.source: Use this to set the route source
fields_help.destination: Use this to set the route destination
fields_help.body_name: Use this to filter for bodies with a name matching ie Sol would match Sol but not Solati 6.
fields_help.station_name: Use this to filter for stations with a word matching in the name
fields_help.reference_coords: Use this instead of Reference System to indicate which coordinates you want to search relative to (for distances etc).
fields_help.reference_route: Use this to indicate a route syou want to search relative to (for distances etc).
fields_help.reference_system: Use this to indicate which system you want to search relative to (for distances etc).
fields_help.system_name: Use this to filter for bodies in a system with a word matching ie Col would match Col 285 Sector IY-W b16-6 but not Colonia.

fleet-carrier.description: This page will allow you to plot between two different star systems for your fleet carrier.  The result will show you every system you need to route to.  It will also let you know when you should gather more fuel.  Time estimates are based on 20 minutes per jump and yielding 150 tonnes of tritium per hour mining for a single player.
fleet-carrier.import_destinations_description: Import a waypoint file from EDSM as a set of destinations (A simple text file with one system name per line).
fleet-carrier.title: Fleet Carrier Router
fleet-carrier.warning: This router will allow you to plot a fleet carrier route between systems

plotter.description: This page will allow you to plot between two different star systems.  The result will show you every time you need to go to the galaxy map in order to plot a new route (for instance when you are at a neutron star).  It will prioritise neutron stars so should be avoided for journeys which are lower than 500 light years (It will likely try to route you to Jackson's Lighthouse first if you're in the bubble).
plotter.title: Neutron Router
plotter.warning: If you have a low maximum range (10-20 LY) you may end up using a boosted jump into a system which you do not have enough range to jump out of.  You should be careful when plotting using this and check that you can get out of the system when you are on the galaxy map.
plotter.exact_plotter: If you are looking for a more complete plotter which includes refuelling, secondary neutron stars and FSD injection then use the new Galaxy Plotter

riches.warning: You should decide if you want to DSS (Detailed Surface Scanner which requires you to travel to the body in system and surface map) or simply FSS (Full Spectrum Scanner from the system jump in point).  FSS is faster for each system but will pay substantially less credits.  The checkbox for "Use Mapping Value" will rank bodies by DSS reward rather then FSS reward.
